# Mobile Casual — Project Configuration

## Project Overview
- **Unity Version:** 2022.3 LTS
- **Render Pipeline:** URP (optimized for mobile)
- **Genre:** Casual puzzle / hyper-casual
- **Target Platform:** iOS + Android
- **Target FPS:** 30 (60 on high-end)

## Architecture

### Assembly Structure
```
MyGame.Core         — events, pooling, utilities
MyGame.Gameplay     — game mechanics, scoring, progression
MyGame.UI           — menus, HUD, popups, shop
MyGame.Systems      — audio, save, analytics, ads, IAP
MyGame.Editor       — level editor tools
```

### Key Systems
- **Game Loop** — simple state machine (Menu → Playing → GameOver → Menu)
- **Scoring** — score + combo multiplier, high score persistence
- **Progression** — level unlock, star rating, currency
- **Touch Input** — tap, swipe, drag via Input System
- **Monetization** — ad integration points (interstitial, rewarded), IAP hooks
- **Analytics** — event tracking hooks (level_start, level_complete, ad_watched)

### Scene Structure
- `S_Bootstrap` — persistent services
- `S_MainMenu` — play button, settings, shop
- `S_Game` — single game scene (levels loaded as config, not separate scenes)

## Skills to Load
- `mobile` — ASTC textures, draw call budget, thermal management, safe areas
- `ui-toolkit` — responsive UI, safe area handling
- `save-system` — PlayerPrefs for settings, JSON for progress
- `object-pooling` — pool everything that spawns
- `state-machine` — game state management
- `audio` — compressed audio, pooled sources
- `addressables` — optional content download

## Rules
Follow all rules in `.codex-legacy/rules/`.

## Key Conventions
- **Performance budget:** <100 draw calls, <50k triangles, <150MB memory
- **Texture sizes:** 512 max for UI, 256 for game objects, ASTC compression
- **Audio:** ADPCM for SFX, Vorbis quality 40% for music, load on demand
- **No LINQ anywhere** — manual loops only
- **Pool everything** — no runtime Instantiate/Destroy during gameplay
- **Target 30fps** for battery life, unlock 60fps as option
- **Safe area** — all UI respects Screen.safeArea for notched devices
- **Build size** — target <100MB initial download, Addressables for extra content
- **Touch input** — minimum tap target 44x44pt, swipe threshold 50px
- **Offline-first** — game works without internet, sync when available

## Input Map
```
Player:
  Tap — Primary Touch
  Swipe — Touch Delta
  Drag — Touch Press + Position
```

